data.title: Louise McGillivray - Women's Golf
data.meta_description: Louise McGillivray - 2013-14: Was 1-of-3 athletes to compete in at least seven tournaments or more … Finished 7th-place or better in four of her seven events
data.text:
2013-14: Was 1-of-3 athletes to compete in at least seven tournaments or more … Finished 7th-place or better in four of her seven events … Held team low-round of 158 (14-over) at the Ashland University Invitational (10/7) placing 5th-out-of-90 overall … McGillivray’s best finish came at the Wellesley Invitational (9/7) after firing an impressive two-day 158 (7-over) and a 4th–place finish … Gathered a pair of spring Top-10 finishes at the Westchester Invitational (7th, 29-over) and the Amherst Invitational (4th, 12-over).

2012-13: Competed in all nine events … Posted a low round of 77 ... Shot a season-best 77-79=156 at Wellesley to start the season strong ... Averaged an 82 on the year.

2010-2012: Played two season at Carson-Newman College before transferring to Merrimack.

Before Merrimack: Won the Banchory Golf Club Ladies Club Championship in 2009, 2010 and 2011 ... Won the Paul Lawrie girls matchplay championship in 2010 ... Started playing for Scotland at the age of 16 ... Graduated with a 4.0 overall grade point average.
